  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@samouss I think the support for `Infinity` is linked to the fact that it is provided in the base values (`start`) that as an implementer you want to reuse because it is previous state and you only ever update one part of the range per user interaction.\r\n\r\nThis `start` variable shouldn't contain values that are not compatible with refine. Therefore, another option could be that the start contains only `number|undefined` values.",
